values.1:
Add diced orange followed
by chunks of lemon.

Top the glass with a slice
of lime and finish with a
sprinkling of equa leaves.
values.2:
Add some chocolate and
warm it in an oven, then
add fresh cream.

Finally sprinkle with
chocolate dust.
values.3:
Add diced pineapple then
top with fresh cream.

Heat the drink briefly
in a warm oven before
serving.
values.4: Simply top with slices of\nfresh lemon to finish this\nlight and refreshing mix.
values.5:
Add chunks of pineapple
followed by diced lime.

Finish the drink by placing
a single slice of orange on
top.
values.6:
Add a sprinkling of equa
leaves followed by a single
lime slice to finish this
gnome classic.
values.7:
Add pineapple chunks to
the drink.

Finally finish this magical
concoction with slices of lime.

values.1:
Add to the bowl four
bars of chocolate and
one sprig of equa leaves.

Bake the bowl in the oven
once more.

Mix in two portions of
fresh cream and finally
finish with a sprinkling of
chocolate dust.
values.2:
Add to the bowl...
 4 pairs of toad's legs
 2 portions of cheese
 2 sprigs of equa leaves
 2 dashes of gnome spice
 1 bunch of dwellberries

Bake the dish in the oven
once more prior to serving.
values.3:
Add to the bowl four king
worms, two onions and a
dash of gnome spices.

Bake the bowl in the oven
once more.

To finish the dish simply
add a topping of equa
leaves.
values.4:
Add to the bowl two
onions, two potatos and
a dash of gnome spices.

Bake the bowl in the oven
once more.

To finish the dish simply
add a topping of equa
leaves.
values.5:
Mix into the dough balls
two king worms, one
sprig of equa leaves and
a shake of gnome spices.

Bake the crunchies for a
short time in the oven.

Add the finishing touch
with a sprinkling of gnome
spices.
values.6:
Break up two bars of
chocolate and mix these
with the balls of dough.

Next add a little gnome
spice to each ball.

Bake the crunchies for a
short time in the oven.

Top the crunchies with a
sprinkling of chocolate dust
to finish.
values.7:
Add three teaspoons of
spice and two sprigs of
equa leaves to the dough
balls.

Bake the crunchies for a
short time in the oven.

Sprinkle a little gnome spice
over the cookies to finish.
values.8:
Mix into the dough balls
two pairs of toad's legs
and a shake of gnome
spices.

Bake the crunchies for a
short time in the oven.

Finish the crunchies with
a sprinkling of equa leaves.
values.9:
Take one lightly spiced
king worm and a little
cheese.  Add these to the
batta before briefly baking
it in the oven once more.

Finish the batta with a
topping of equa leaves.
values.10:
Put the plain batta to
one side.  Next take
some prime toad's legs,
season these with equa
leaves and gnome spice.

Add the seasoned toad's legs
along with some cheese to
the batta.

Bake the batta in the oven
once more and serve hot.
values.11:
Top the plain batta with
equal quantities of cheese
and tomato.

Place the batta in the
oven once more until all
the cheese has melted.

Finish the dish with a
sprinkling of equa leaves.
values.12:
Lay four sprigs of equa
leaves on top of the batta
before baking it in the
oven once more.

Top the batta with chunks
of pineapple, orange and
lime.

Finish the batta with a
sprinkling of gnome spices.
values.13:
Add to the plain batta
two tomatos, one onion,
one cabbage and some
dwellberries.

 Top the batta with cheese
and briefly place it in the
oven once more.

Finish the dish with a
sprinkling of equa leaves.
